Let there be a list called "scores" that begins empty.
Remember 85 as scores.
Remember 92 as scores.
Remember 78 as scores.
Remember 90 as scores.
Remember 88 as scores.

Let there be a number called "total" that equals the sum of scores.
Let there be a number called "count" that equals the length of scores.
Let there be a number called "average" that equals total divided by count.

Say "The five scores are:".
Print scores, separated by ", ".
Say "Their average is:".
Print average.
